I think the most hopeful point mentioned thus far is like whizbang says, times change.<br>
<br>
At the root of this issue is one simple point:<br>
<br>
Verant said:<br>
&quot;When it comes to dishing out damage, wizards have no rival.&quot;<br>
<br>
That was never true, not under anything but the most limited and extreme circumstance. While maybe its becoming arguably more accurate with luclin, its still not true, and the longer the fight goes, the more obvious that becomes.<br>
<br>
Abashi once tried to explain that description (note, verant changed that description at least 3 times prior to the most recent revamp of their webpage) by stating the following (rough translation, i cant find the post atm)<br>
<br>
&quot;That means wizards can do the most damage in X amount of time. It never meant that wizards could do more damage in a full bar of mana than other casters, in fact, almost all other casters can outdamage wizards.&quot;<br>
<br>
That's the vision apparently. In terms of a single shot nuke, not counting debuffs or pet damage in the same amount of time, apparently wizards meet the vision. (Of course, thats not even true either, because there are level gaps during which mages can out nuke us, etc).<br>
<br>
But, if you take a level 60 wizard, and stand them up against other casters, yes they have a bigger nuke and in the time it takes to cast that nuke, they can outdamage other casters (discounting pets and resists, etc).<br>
<br>
~~<br>
<br>
