<br>
We need to play, in my old MUD terms, &quot;gameload to gameload&quot; instead of &quot;gameload to godload.&quot; <br>
<br>
Melees get increases from GEAR, while your 25% DD reduction is non-gear related.  The addition of more right-click droppables addresses this, but as you say: &quot;apples to apples.&quot;<br>
<br>
Nice analysis.<br>
<br>
<br>
-Szii Uln'hyrr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uestsunforge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>est sunforge</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/3/02 7:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixing wizards: my recommendations (long)</span><hr size=1> I can actually agree with points a-f + h of this, but I'm not that comfortable with the whole medding-while-standing thing. I'm not sure why exactly, but it just feels wrong. (Unless perhaps you have to be standing stock still for more than 2 secs or so in order to focus yourself or something similar)<br>
<br>
The lack of clicky items at lower levels annoyed the socks off me when I was younger, as most of my melee friends had proc'ing items already, and as if I was gonna use something in melee after about level 25. It just wasn't worth it. Casters need nice clicky items at the mid-levels in my opinion, it's nice to get some toys to encourage you to keep playing.<br>
<br>
est.<br>
